CNCP v1 23548
{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#14490: shallowReactive with v-for incorrect typing: property does not exist on type true",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:15:40.586748+00:00",
  "text": "shallowReactive with v-for incorrect typing: property does not exist on type true\n\n### Vue version\n\n@ea24576\n\n### Link to minimal reproduction\n\nhttps://play.vuejs.org/#\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nshallowReactive object gets incorrectly typed when used in v-for:\n```vue\n<script setup>\nimport { shallowReactive } from 'vue'\n\nconst obj = shallowReactive({\n  a: { title: 'A' },\n  b: { title: 'B' },\n})\n</script>\n\n<template>\n  <h1 v-for=\"item in obj\">{{ item.title }}</h1>\n  <!--                            ^^^^^\n  -->\n</template>\n```\n\n### What is expected?\n\nNo error, and\n```ts\ntypeof item // { title: string }\n```\n\n### What is actually happening?\n\nTypescript error:\n```\nProperty 'title' does not exist on type 'true | { title: string; } | { title: string; }'.\n  Property 'title' does not exist on type 'true' .ts(2339)\n```\n\n### System Info\n\n```shell\n\n```\n\n### Any additional comments?\n\nI found these typings in vue, I guess it might come from here\n```ts\ndeclare const ShallowReactiveMarker: unique symbol;\nexport type ShallowReactive<T> = T & {\n    [ShallowReactiveMarker]?: true;\n};\n```",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    "scope: types"
  ],
